For a rogue to be useful at least 1 good tank and a cleric are CRITICAL. Have you seen the damage a rogue does when they aren't BSing? Pretty weak. If a rogue isn't BSing, they may as well be fletching as far as damage output is concerned.<br>
<br>
It's pretty simple, we need mana to do damage, rogues need a support crew. <p><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 44th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 3:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> I think the point everyone seems to miss in this whole group argument is the level of assistance rogues need to operate at all vs. the level wizards need.  Can a 60 level rogue kill a blue?  No.  Can a 60 level wiz kill a blue?  Yes, easily.  So how much assistance is that rogue getting from that cleric and warrior?  A lot.  How much assistance is that wizard getting?  A little, but it doesn't matter, she didn't need any before.  If clerics and chanters improved wizards to the level that clerics and warriors improve a rogue, nobody would ever play a rogue.  Since rogues can solo greens without help and high blues with help, wizards would go from med blues to low reds.  Wow, single wizard in the group and you can spank trak.  That sounds fair.<br>
<br>
Wizards keep lamenting that they can't seem to keep up with pulls.  Oh, I see, three melee being healed by a cleric beating on a mob that was slowed by the chanter and your going to cry becuase you can't keep up with the five of them?  You only need to do 1/6th the total damage to be equal.  Standard 8k krup knight in guk, you do one SS and you've done your job.  The melee better do more damage than you or they aren't earning that support they are getting just to be able to do their jobs!  This means the three melee have to do the other 5/6ths or nearly twice as much as you do to earn their keep.  <br>
<br>
On large raids, it's pretty much standard procedure for the raid leader to ask the wizzies to &quot;make it dead&quot; when something's 60-70% alive.  Most high level raids don't go very well without a good wizzy turn out.  We are very good at debuffing HPs in less than 30 secs.  Something that takes a lot more melee/clerics to acheive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wardaemon>Wardaemon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 4:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> A rogue does NOT require a tank and a cleric to do effective damage.  A rogue and a ranger, for example, can make a vicious outdoor combination.  Ranger can snare,<br>
Rogue can Instill Doubt, and what do you know, you're fear kiting... (and backstabbing for 400+ per hit)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1324<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 4:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> A lot of this argument is being segmented into specific level and location types.  First you get one side saying Rogues are awful without backstab (you have other's hits off don't you?  You have to, because the quads and streaming constancy of hits is impossible to read) and cannot survive without a Cleric or Warrior.  Well, that's patently absurd, we all know Rogues do not die the instant they get into a battle without a Cleric to heal and a Warrior to taunt.  I play a Rogue, I know its true.<br>
<br>
The other side wants to say that Wizards are trash because Rogues can outdamage them using their best gear, that Wizards bring only damage to a group.  The fact is, few rogues in Norrath can hope to do that absurd level of damage because it requires the ABSOLUTE BEST gear in the planet to try, and only at a certain level.<br>
<br>
That's why I tend not to use roges vs Wizards as an example of problems with the class.  The problem isn't so much &quot;he outdamages me!&quot; because nearly every class in the GAME can outdamage a Wizard in the time it takes for him to regain all his mana after a full burn.  The problem isn't &quot;rogues replace me in groups!&quot; because these are two different but similar jobs.  Rogues make the monsters hps erode away quickly and steadily, Wizards make it go away in big explosions and have a few other little toys to work with.<br>
<br>
The problem is this:  Wizards were designed with a certain concept and idea by Verant and very few levels are they able to do this.  Further, this concept and use is eroded by the fact that melee has been enhanced (by Verant's own admission now, remember) to the point that the damage output they can bring actually has made damage casters fairly weak.<br>
<br>
The argument in favor of Wizards doing well is always &quot;we can do 1293124 damage in 34.451235 seconds!! nobody can do that!!! lets see a rogue do 2k!!!!!&quot;  And that is just silly.  First off, logs prove otherwise, I have NEVER, EVER seen a log that showed the Wizard blasting as much damage as the best melee class, so lets just lay that aside guys.  Secondly, nobody, Concussion spell or not, C2 and bardsong or not, NOBODY can blast constantly and lay down huge damage on every single monster.  It just can't be done.<br>
<br>
So looking at the damage output is like someone shooting a target with 5 minutes to prepare and no wind.  Sure, he's deadly, he hits that bullseye every time.  Now put him in a smoky firefight with a beat up M16 and guys shooting at him with no time to aim, how good is he then?  The actuality of the game negates the apparent huge advantage Wizards have.<br>
<br>
And please, lets put soloing aside, that is a separate issue entirely.  Beryl if you are hunting things you can kill solo with your Wizard, you are hunting the wrong damn things.  Soloing and grouping are two different concepts, if you want to try to prove that being able to solo to level 60 makes you balanced in a grouping game that REQUIRES you to group to achieve anything useful you can try but we are talking about something entirely different here.<br>
<br>
Something that I keep having to say, that makes me sigh inside every single time I see it is that not every single Wizard in the game is level 60 in an Uberguild with an epic in their fist.  Saying that Bane or Sunstrike or any other single damn spell at level 60 balances the class, using that as an example of how things are fine is the most annoying thing that comes out of the mouth of Wizards and other players.  Thankfully, unlike the idiocy before Kunark, NOBODY but a Wizard thinks that the level 60 blasts somehow fix the class, they are usualy amazed the damage is SO LOW.  I used to see all the time how Ice Comet made everything fine.  48 levels are screwed up and Ice Comet fixes it all.  Sorry, that's just not true, and you should know better.<br>
<br>
Please, lets try to think about this a little more lucidly, there isn't a single honest Wizard in the game that can say &quot;everything is fine with my class and no changes can be done!&quot;  Just as there isn't a single honest Wizard in the game that can say &quot;This class is utter trash and worthless in every group!&quot;<br>
<br>
Sit back, think a little bit about it, and try to see both sides.  Yes, that means you with the Epic in your hand as well as you with the Gossimer Robe and Giant Snake Fang.  Wizards need work.  Attacking fellow Wizards with mockery and anger doesn't help that, and neither does screams of how Wizards are awful.<br>
<br>
In my fairly experienced opinion, Verant won't fix us.  They will never, ever do what needs to be done (which is sad, because it ain't that much), but they will do minor other things along the way that will be kinda nifty.  But at the very least we can have an intelligent, rational and charitable discussion about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uellocopato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ellocopato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 4:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> &quot;Dood, uhm.... You did mention soloing... Read your post again....... You just didn't say the word solo..... &quot;<br>
<br>
No... I said we do not another specific class to do our damage.  A rogue does.  Re-read my post again.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umarktodd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarkTodd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 5:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> &quot;A wizard does not need another person. He can root &amp; nuke, or snare and kite.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sounds like soloing. If this is not what you meant, then perhaps you could clarify.<br>
<br>
 <p>Merkus Stormcrow (40, High Elf, Mostly Retired Wizard)
<BR>
Knorm Knimbleknife
(21, Dwarf, Rogue)
<BR>
Rukus (6, Half-elven, Bongo Banging Bard)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uellocopato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ellocopato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 6:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> The point I was trying to make is that our damage dealing is not dependent on another class or any specific class for that matter.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Lack of a cleric can be overcome, lack of a tank can be overcome.<br>
<br>
A rogue's ability to backstab is dependent on someone keeping the mob occupied so he can get behind him and do his damage.<br>
<br>
We do not need that<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaradin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 7:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> ellocopato, Samadhi, and Rombus:<br>
<br>
Actually you CAN include Enchanters. Their spell (Clarity and Clarity II) heal our mana like a cleric's heal spell gives a Rogue HPs. The difference is that the heal spell is instaneous while Clarity II is slow like a snail.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, a Wizard DOES need a tank. I'd like to see you guys do an all caster raid ...I'll even give you the benefit of the doubt and say a Bane-able MoB. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Prove me wrong by doing a raid (worthy of your level) w/ NO tank and I'll believe you ...till than your giving us fluff!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Cleric is questionable, but I still think we need a Cleric. Assuming you want that heal or rez.<br>
<br>
<br>
Far as normal XP grinding groups, I have seen Rogues tank fairly well. They are better mana sinks than Warriors no doubt about that. If you are gonna argue a Tank to maximize damage for that Rogue than you must factor in an Enchanter/Bard/Necro for us to Maximize our damage ...or take your Shaman.<br>
<br>
Wizards need about the same or even more than Rogues in group settings.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Pride is clouding the issue here.<br>
<br>
